North Mugirango MP Charles Geni (pictured) wants the government to reveal the whereabouts of Sh1.4 billion donated by the Kuwait government to re-build schools destroyed in the 2007-08 post-poll violence.The MP said the money was not released by the Treasury to rebuild the affected schools in Nyamira county. &ldquo; For 10 years now, we have been waiting to see the cash released to the beneficiary schools, but no one is talking about it. Kenyans should get an explanation on how the money was spent,&rdquo; the MP said.The MP spoke in his constituency on Wednesday where he issued bursary cheques for Sh17 million to needy students in various schools and colleges. He said the money may have been misappropriated.